  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-pistachio-pesto/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle and peel your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Strip your <strong>mint leaves </strong>from their stems, discard the stems</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-pistachio-pesto/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato & mozzarella tortelloni </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 2-3 min, then add your <strong>blanched peas</strong> to the pot and cook for 1 min further or until the tortelloni is cooked with a slight bite and the peas are refreshed</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked tomato & mozzarella tortelloni </strong>and<strong> refreshed peas</strong>, reserve the pot and a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-pistachio-pesto/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Set aside a few<strong> basil </strong>and <strong>mint leaves</strong> and <strong>half </strong>of your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese </strong>for garnish (you'll use the rest later!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-pistachio-pesto/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>peeled garlic</strong>,<strong> pistachio nuts</strong>, the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong>, <strong>remaining basil </strong>(including the stalks), and<strong> remaining mint leaves </strong>to a <strong>food processor</strong></p><p>Add the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s]</strong>, 2 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 1/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 1/4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-pistachio-pesto/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Blitz until you are left with a smooth paste – this is your<strong> pistachio pesto</strong></p><p>Tip: No food processor? Chop everything up as finely as you can and mix it together!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-pistachio-pesto/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat and add the<strong> drained tomato & mozzarella tortelloni</strong> <strong>and peas</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>pistachio pesto</strong> and stir gently until the pasta is coated in the pesto and everything is warmed through – this is your <strong>pistachio pesto with tomato & mozzarella tortelloni</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p><p>Cut the<strong> remaining lemon </strong>into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-pistachio-pesto/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pistachio pesto with tomato & mozzarella tortelloni </strong>with the <strong>reserved grated Italian hard cheese</strong> on top and a<strong> lemon wedge</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved mint</strong> and <strong>basil leaves</strong>, a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
